  "summary": "A same-concurrency HTTPS proxy diagnostic was added and run with concurrency=8 across all three benchmark scenarios. The libcurl concurrent baseline uses one libcurl multi handle with eight easy handles and explicit maxconnects/max-host/max-total connection limits set to the same concurrency. The diagnostic is opt-in and separated from the canonical SOTA matrix. It refutes the hypothesis that matching a concurrent library model alone exposes a ylong SOTA advantage: ylong throughput geomean is 0.842x of libcurl, worst cell is 0.733x, CPU/request geomean is 2.065x, and RSS max ratio is 1.842x.",
